    <div>
        <div class="col-lg-5">
            <div>
                <h3>Why is it called The Sun?</h3>
                The Sun is the name of the star that is in the center of our solar system.  <br>
                Its name comes from the old english sonne which comes from the German word Sonne. [<a href="#ref1">1</a>]<br>
                Other names include the Greek Helios and the Latin Sol. [<a href="#ref1">1</a>]
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3>How was The Sun created?</h3>
                The Sun was formed about 4.5 billion years ago after gravity had compressed particles of gas and dust together under the force of gravity. [<a href="#ref2">2</a>]<br>
                The mass of particles eventually started to spin an flatten out creating a protostar. [<a href="#ref2">2</a>]<br>
                Eventually this formed into what we know as The Sun.
            </div>

        </div>

