    <div>
        <h3>What are Solar Winds and Solar Flares?</h3>
        The Sun produces solar winds which can reach speeds of up to 500 miles (800 kilometers) per second. <br>
        The material the winds carry large amounts of radiation towards the earth which would cause extreme damage, but the Earth is protected from this radiation due to the Earth's magnetosphere. [<a href="#ref8">8</a>]<br>
        Another thing the Sun can do is called a solar flare which is a burst of energy from the Sun’s surface. [<a href="#ref8">8</a>]<br>
        These can cause events on earth such as auroras but can also cause problems with radio communication and power outages. [<a href="#ref9">9</a>]
    </div>
    <div>
        <h3>What are Solar Eclipses?</h3>
        The Sun will also periodically have a solar eclipse which happens when the moon gets between the Earth and the Sun which casts a shadow on the Earth. [<a href="#ref10">10</a>]<br>
        Solar eclipses come in one of four forms being either total, annular, partial, and hybrid each having a different amount of the sun being blocked. [<a href="#ref10">10</a>]<br>
        It is important to remeber that even though some of the Sun is blocked does not mean that it is safe to look at it without protection. [<a href="#ref10">10</a>]
    </div>
