    <div>
        <h3>Other Facts</h3>
        For a long time up until the 16th century it was widely regarded that Earth was the center of the Solar System until the Polish astronomer Nicolai Copernicus wrote a model that described why the Sun must be the center of our Solar System. [<a href="#ref11">11</a>]<br>
        People used to tell times using an object called a sun dial which used the Sun's light to cast a shadow on the dial's face which would look similar to modern day clocks.<br>
        The Sun is also an important part of some religions including Egyptian, Indo-European, and Meso-American. [<a href="#ref12">12</a>]
    </div>
